all the information into one
giant database powered by AI

258
00:12:54.483 --> 00:12:56.693
and selling the data
to the highest bidder.

259
00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:59.654
Marius Cole is
completely eradicating

260
00:12:59.696 --> 00:13:01.114
the basic concept of privacy.

261
00:13:01.198 --> 00:13:02.991
and people don't even
realize it.

262
00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:04.993
So you see yourself
as a whistleblower?

263
00:13:05.035 --> 00:13:07.704
I tried. but Natalie caught me.

264
00:13:07.788 --> 00:13:09.498
So because of Natalie.
you're facing

265
00:13:09.539 --> 00:13:10.957
some pretty stiff penalties.

266
00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:12.626
I wouldn't hurt Natalie.
for God's sake.

267
00:13:12.751 --> 00:13:14.961
I'm the good guy here.
not the villain.

268
00:13:15.045 --> 00:13:17.672
Ooh. people who say that
make me nervous.

269
00:13:17.798 --> 00:13:19.883
I didn't blame Natalie.

270
00:13:19.966 --> 00:13:22.302
She was a total techno-optimist.

271
00:13:22.385 --> 00:13:24.596
She truly believed that. if
it were harder for bad people

272
00:13:24.679 --> 00:13:26.848
to hide. the world would be
a safer place.

273
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:29.309
All that being said.
where were you two nights ago?

274
00:13:29.434 --> 00:13:32.103
I was at a concert
at Madison Square Garden.

275
00:13:32.229 --> 00:13:33.814
The amount of surveillance
in that place.

276
00:13:33.897 --> 00:13:35.315
you can verify that
100 different ways.

277
00:13:37.234 --> 00:13:38.819
Okay. We will be in touch.

278
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:40.612
Wait.

279
00:13:40.654 --> 00:13:43.865
A few days before I was canned.
so about a week ago.

280
00:13:43.949 --> 00:13:46.827
I ran into Natalie at a café.

281
00:13:46.910 --> 00:13:48.537
She was with a guy.

282
00:13:48.662 --> 00:13:51.540
And when I went over to say hi.
she got super weird.

283
00:13:51.581 --> 00:13:53.041
Do you know who the guy was?

284
00:13:53.125 --> 00:13:54.459
I didn't recognize him.

285
00:13:54.543 --> 00:13:58.964
But something
about the vibe was off.

286
00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:01.424
I got the security video
from the café.

287
00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:03.885
All right. Good.

288
00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:08.181
So this is the date and time
our wannabe whistleblower

289
00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:10.517
said he ran into Natalie
and the mystery man.

290
00:14:13.103 --> 00:14:14.312
There he is right there.

291
00:14:18.567 --> 00:14:20.402
And there she is.

292
00:14:29.995 --> 00:14:31.329
Looks like she's crying.

293
00:14:31.455 --> 00:14:33.248
Can you zoom in
on the guy's face?

294
00:14:33.331 --> 00:14:35.041
I'll run facial rec.

295
00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:42.632
Sean Morris.

296
00:14:42.757 --> 00:14:44.301
I'm Detective Riley.

297
00:14:44.342 --> 00:14:46.470
This is Detective Walker. NYPD.

298
00:14:46.553 --> 00:14:49.222
We'd like to ask you a few
questions about Natalie Wallis.

299
00:14:49.264 --> 00:14:50.682
Good.

300
00:14:50.765 --> 00:14:52.767
I'm glad to hear
she went through with it.

301
00:14:52.851 --> 00:14:54.561
Went through with what?

302
00:14:56.313 --> 00:14:57.689
Wait. what is this about?

303
00:14:57.814 --> 00:14:59.691
We're Homicide detectives.

304
00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:02.402
Natalie Wallis was murdered
two nights ago.

305
00:15:02.527 --> 00:15:04.571
My God.

306
00:15:04.654 --> 00:15:05.697
I didn't know.

307
00:15:05.822 --> 00:15:08.700
I've been at a yoga retreat.

308
00:15:08.784 --> 00:15:11.453
I was with her earlier that day.

309
00:15:11.495 --> 00:15:13.997
Were you two in a relationship?

310
00:15:14.122 --> 00:15:16.917
What... God. No.

311
00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:19.294
I'm gay.

312
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.339
I'm a trauma counselor
at the Midtown Women's Clinic.

313
00:15:22.422 --> 00:15:23.799
I was helping her.

314
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:25.967
Helping her with what?

315
00:15:26.009 --> 00:15:28.345
Natalie was sexually assaulted

316
00:15:28.428 --> 00:15:29.888
about a month ago.

317
00:15:29.922 --> 00:15:31.882
And when we last spoke.

318
00:15:32.073 --> 00:15:34.868
she said she was gonna go
to the police.

319
00:15:41.121 --> 00:15:43.957
You said the rape occurred
a month prior to her murder.

320
00:15:44.038 --> 00:15:45.105
That's what we were told.

321
00:15:45.130 --> 00:15:47.992
Normally. what we see with
a post-sexual-assault situation

322
00:15:48.034 --> 00:15:50.954
are lacerations or abrasions
to the posterior fourchette

323
00:15:51.079 --> 00:15:52.831
or the fossa navicularis.

324
00:15:52.872 --> 00:15:54.833
But because of the increased
blood flow to those areas

325
00:15:54.958 --> 00:15:57.293
naturally.
they tend to heal quickly.

326
00:15:57.418 --> 00:15:59.129
Unless the injuries are severe.
they usually abate

327
00:15:59.254 --> 00:16:00.547
within a week or two.

328
00:16:00.630 --> 00:16:01.840
So you can't tell us
one way or the other?

329
00:16:01.881 --> 00:16:03.258
Not conclusively.

330
00:16:03.383 --> 00:16:05.885
But I was able to perform
a secondary examination

331
00:16:05.927 --> 00:16:07.637
and found something else.

332
00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:10.974
You see this slight
discoloration here and here?

333
00:16:11.057 --> 00:16:12.934
- Not really.
- It's very faint.

334
00:16:13.017 --> 00:16:15.520
But it appears to be ecchymosis.

335
00:16:15.562 --> 00:16:18.314
That's the yellowing you see
at the very final stages

336
00:16:18.398 --> 00:16:20.191
of the body
breaking down hemoglobin

337
00:16:20.275 --> 00:16:21.526
pooled under the skin.

338
00:16:21.609 --> 00:16:23.278
So she had bruises.

339
00:16:23.361 --> 00:16:25.029
On both wrists and her throat.

340
00:16:25.155 --> 00:16:26.531
almost completely healed.

341
00:16:26.614 --> 00:16:28.199
which is why we didn't
catch it initially.

342
00:16:28.324 --> 00:16:30.326
- Okay. Anything else?
- Yes.

343
00:16:30.410 --> 00:16:32.829
She tested positive
for hepatitis B.

344
00:16:32.954 --> 00:16:34.289
Appears to be recent too.

345
00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:35.832
According to her
medical records.

346
00:16:35.915 --> 00:16:37.417
she tested negative for all STDs

347
00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:39.961
at her last checkup
three months ago.

348
00:16:40.044 --> 00:16:41.337
All right.
Thanks. Doc.

349
00:16:41.421 --> 00:16:42.881
Thank you.

350
00:16:42.964 --> 00:16:45.175
So her rapist
figures out somehow

351
00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:47.218
that she was gonna report him

352
00:16:47.302 --> 00:16:50.013
and kills her
before she gets the chance.

353
00:16:50.096 --> 00:16:51.264
We know when the rape occurred.

354
00:16:51.389 --> 00:16:52.724
so we just need to retrace
her steps that day.

355
00:16:52.891 --> 00:16:55.393
find out who she was with.

356
00:16:55.518 --> 00:16:57.395
October 17th. you said?

357
00:16:57.479 --> 00:16:59.022
Yeah. according
to Natalie's calendar app.

358
00:16:59.147 --> 00:17:00.523
you two had dinner that night?

359
00:17:00.607 --> 00:17:02.233
Yeah. yeah. I remember we went

360
00:17:02.358 --> 00:17:05.653
to a new Mediterranean place
that she'd been wanting to try.

361
00:17:05.695 --> 00:17:07.489
Here you go. Thank you so much.

362
00:17:07.572 --> 00:17:10.200
What does this have to do
with her murder?

363
00:17:10.325 --> 00:17:11.576
What was her mood like
that night?

364
00:17:11.659 --> 00:17:12.994
Her... her mood?

365
00:17:13.077 --> 00:17:14.996
Yeah. did she seem upset?

366
00:17:15.038 --> 00:17:16.498
Mention any problems
she was having?

367
00:17:16.664 --> 00:17:18.166
No.

368
00:17:18.291 --> 00:17:20.710
No. we mostly just talked
about the reality shows

369
00:17:20.752 --> 00:17:25.048
we were watching
and bitched about our jobs.

370
00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:28.218
She mention anything
about a sexual assault?

371
00:17:28.301 --> 00:17:31.638
What? No.

372
00:17:31.679 --> 00:17:34.974
Why? Did something happen?

373
00:17:35.058 --> 00:17:36.684
We're not sure.

374
00:17:39.437 --> 00:17:41.481
What happened
after dinner that night?

375
00:17:43.441 --> 00:17:44.943
Nothing.

376
00:17:45.026 --> 00:17:47.862
She had to leave early
because of some sort

377
00:17:47.946 --> 00:17:49.531
of emergency that came up
with one of the projects

378
00:17:49.656 --> 00:17:51.908
she was working on.

379
00:17:51.950 --> 00:17:53.159
So she went back
to the Utomnia office?

380
00:17:54.619 --> 00:17:57.956
Marius texted her
while we were eating.

381
00:17:58.081 --> 00:17:59.624
I don't work
at the company anymore.

382
00:17:59.707 --> 00:18:01.751
so she couldn't tell me
what it was about.

383
00:18:01.835 --> 00:18:05.421
But she had
to cut the meal short

384
00:18:05.547 --> 00:18:07.257
to go meet up with him.

385
00:18:10.718 --> 00:18:12.345
What the hell is this?

386
00:18:12.428 --> 00:18:15.515
You have no right to...
this is completely unwarranted!

387
00:18:15.598 --> 00:18:18.810
No. actually. it's entirely
warranted. literally.

388
00:18:18.935 --> 00:18:20.562
This is an invasion
of my privacy.

389
00:18:20.645 --> 00:18:22.272
Yeah. sucks. doesn't it?

390
00:18:22.313 --> 00:18:25.358
Got a prescription here
for lamivudine.

391
00:18:25.441 --> 00:18:26.860
It's got your name on it.

392
00:18:26.943 --> 00:18:28.153
What's that for?

393
00:18:28.236 --> 00:18:29.571
It's none of your damn business.

394
00:18:29.696 --> 00:18:32.574
Well. the internet says
hepatitis B medication.

395
00:18:32.657 --> 00:18:35.994
Detectives. we found a box
of ammunition under a bed.

396
00:18:36.035 --> 00:18:37.620
9 millimeter.

397
00:18:37.662 --> 00:18:42.292
Same caliber used
to kill Natalie Wallis.

398
00:18:42.333 --> 00:18:44.294
- I want my lawyer.
- Yeah. I'll bet you do.

399
00:18:44.377 --> 00:18:45.795
Marius Cole. you're under arrest

400
00:18:45.879 --> 00:18:47.338
for the murder
of Natalie Wallis.

401
00:18:47.422 --> 00:18:49.966
You have the right
to remain silent.

402
00:18:50.133 --> 00:18:52.302
Were the police able
to recover the murder weapon?

403
00:18:52.343 --> 00:18:55.054
No. and Marius Cole
has never had a firearm

404
00:18:55.096 --> 00:18:56.181
registered in his name.

405
00:18:56.222 --> 00:18:57.515
What about motive?

406
00:18:57.599 --> 00:18:59.434
Cole killed Natalie to stop her

407
00:18:59.517 --> 00:19:01.811
from reporting him for rape.

408
00:19:01.895 --> 00:19:03.521
Can we prove that he raped her?

409
00:19:03.605 --> 00:19:05.023
I think so.

410
00:19:05.106 --> 00:19:06.524
It's all based
on circumstantial evidence.

411
00:19:06.608 --> 00:19:07.859
but I think we can get there.

412
00:19:07.942 --> 00:19:09.194
The best news of all
is that we can place

413
00:19:09.319 --> 00:19:10.695
Cole at the murder scene.

414
00:19:10.778 --> 00:19:13.615
DNA tests confirmed
that the hair recovered

415
00:19:13.656 --> 00:19:16.034
from Natalie's body
belongs to him.

416
00:19:16.117 --> 00:19:17.869
It's not a perfect case.

417
00:19:17.911 --> 00:19:20.538
but Cole has no alibi
for the night of the murder.

418
00:19:20.622 --> 00:19:22.832
Marius Cole's donated
millions to various

419
00:19:22.957 --> 00:19:24.542
female-forward charities.

420
00:19:24.584 --> 00:19:27.003
He's got a big reputation
as a liberal feminist ally.

421
00:19:27.086 --> 00:19:30.131
Yeah. which is why
we need to bury him.

422
00:19:30.256 --> 00:19:32.467
A wolf in sheep's clothing
is gonna kill more sheep

423
00:19:32.550 --> 00:19:34.260
if you give him the chance.

424
00:19:38.473 --> 00:19:39.724
Okay.

425
00:19:39.849 --> 00:19:41.851
Charge him with murder 2.

426
00:19:46.022 --> 00:19:47.440
Ms. Maroun.

427
00:19:47.565 --> 00:19:49.234
Your Honor.
the people seek remand.

428
00:19:49.359 --> 00:19:50.902
The defendant is a billionaire.

429
00:19:50.985 --> 00:19:53.071
He has access to a private jet.

430
00:19:53.154 --> 00:19:54.864
There is no amount of bail
that could be set

431
00:19:54.948 --> 00:19:56.908
that could prohibit him
from fleeing the country.

432
00:19:56.991 --> 00:19:58.785
My client is not going anywhere.

433
00:19:58.868 --> 00:20:01.037
But I'll spare us all
the back and forth about bail

434
00:20:01.121 --> 00:20:02.872
because it is a moot point.

435
00:20:02.997 --> 00:20:04.624
The state has no case.

436
00:20:04.707 --> 00:20:07.627
and therefore. I am immediately
filing a motion to dismiss.

437
00:20:07.710 --> 00:20:09.087
On what grounds?

438
00:20:09.170 --> 00:20:11.381
We have irrefutable proof
that Marius Cole

439
00:20:11.442 --> 00:20:14.050
did not commit this murder.

440
00:20:21.561 --> 00:20:23.630
What is it exactly that I'm
looking at here. counselor?

441
00:20:23.655 --> 00:20:26.333
Security camera footage
from Marius Cole's apartment

442
00:20:26.416 --> 00:20:28.626
that shows he was at home
in Tribeca

443
00:20:28.752 --> 00:20:30.503
at the time Natalie Wallis
was murdered.

444
00:20:30.628 --> 00:20:32.589
And what.
the time stamps in the corner

445
00:20:32.630 --> 00:20:34.299
are supposed to be the proof?

446
00:20:34.382 --> 00:20:38.636
As I detailed in my motion.
his brownstone is also equipped

447
00:20:38.720 --> 00:20:41.431
with state-of-the-art
bio scanning technology

448
00:20:41.556 --> 00:20:44.851
that tracks all living beings
in the home at all times.

449
00:20:44.976 --> 00:20:48.271
And its logs show with
a zero degree of uncertainty

450
00:20:48.354 --> 00:20:51.441
that Mr. Cole was in
the apartment the entire night.

451
00:20:51.566 --> 00:20:53.568
- Your Honor...
- Proceeding with a trial

452
00:20:53.693 --> 00:20:55.445
would be a colossal waste

453
00:20:55.487 --> 00:20:57.614
of this court's
limited resources.

454
00:20:57.697 --> 00:20:59.699
to say nothing
of the time and energy

455
00:20:59.783 --> 00:21:02.786
of everyone involved.
not least of all my client.

456
00:21:02.911 --> 00:21:05.747
Marius Cole is the head
of the largest

457
00:21:05.872 --> 00:21:08.208
and the most invasive
surveillance tech firm

458
00:21:08.333 --> 00:21:09.793
in the world.

459
00:21:09.876 --> 00:21:12.837
He has the unlimited resources
and the know-how

460
00:21:12.962 --> 00:21:16.299
to fabricate all of this...
this so-called evidence.

461
00:21:16.424 --> 00:21:18.051
Given the preponderance of it.

462
00:21:18.176 --> 00:21:21.554
there is no way a jury gets
around reasonable doubt.

463
00:21:21.679 --> 00:21:23.973
They will. once I debunk it all.

464
00:21:24.015 --> 00:21:25.141
which is why
they're trying to have

465
00:21:25.183 --> 00:21:27.102
this case tossed on a motion.

466
00:21:27.227 --> 00:21:29.396
I agree with Mr. Price.

467
00:21:29.437 --> 00:21:32.232
You're welcome to present this
evidence at trial. Ms. Calhoun.

468
00:21:32.315 --> 00:21:35.235
but there's no way in hell
I'm dismissing this case.

469
00:21:42.158 --> 00:21:43.910
I have over 20 years
of experience

470
00:21:43.993 --> 00:21:45.995
as a consultant
in cybersecurity.

471
00:21:46.121 --> 00:21:48.915
And the NYPD brought you in
to advise on this case.

472
00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:50.500
Yes.

473
00:21:50.542 --> 00:21:52.502
Shortly after
Natalie Wallis was murdered.

474
00:21:52.627 --> 00:21:55.338
someone hacked into every one
of the devices in her home

475
00:21:55.463 --> 00:21:57.340
and erased any data that had
been recorded in the hours

476
00:21:57.382 --> 00:21:58.758
surrounding her death.

477
00:21:58.842 --> 00:22:01.553
Including video footage
from her security cameras?

478
00:22:01.678 --> 00:22:03.388
They also accessed
the city's mainframe

479
00:22:03.513 --> 00:22:04.973
and wiped
the street camera footage

480
00:22:05.056 --> 00:22:06.516
from Ms. Wallis's block.

481
00:22:06.599 --> 00:22:08.893
I was brought in to do a
digital forensic investigation

482
00:22:09.018 --> 00:22:10.520
to determine who the hacker was.

483
00:22:10.562 --> 00:22:12.272
Were you successful?

484
00:22:12.355 --> 00:22:15.650
No. whoever did it covered
their tracks incredibly well.

485
00:22:15.692 --> 00:22:18.528
In your professional opinion.
does the defendant have

486
00:22:18.653 --> 00:22:21.072
the skills necessary
to have done this?

487
00:22:21.156 --> 00:22:24.159
It's literally a service
Utomnia. his company.

488
00:22:24.242 --> 00:22:25.827
offers to its clients.

489
00:22:25.910 --> 00:22:27.704
The level of hacking
we're talking about here

490
00:22:27.746 --> 00:22:29.247
for Marius Cole would be like

491
00:22:29.289 --> 00:22:31.374
Stephen Hawking doing a Sudoku.

492
00:22:31.458 --> 00:22:33.835
What about
manufacturing evidence.

493
00:22:33.877 --> 00:22:38.131
like video surveillance footage
or digital location data.

494
00:22:38.256 --> 00:22:39.799
Is that also something
Utomnia does?

495
00:22:39.924 --> 00:22:41.259
I don't think
they advertise that.

496
00:22:41.384 --> 00:22:43.344
but they certainly have
the capabilities.

497
00:22:43.470 --> 00:22:46.890
So hypothetically.
the defendant could create

498
00:22:46.973 --> 00:22:49.392
proof for an alibi
that was not real.

499
00:22:49.476 --> 00:22:51.352
- Absolutely.
- Objection. Your Honor.

500
00:22:51.436 --> 00:22:53.730
Assumes facts not in evidence.

501
00:22:53.813 --> 00:22:57.317
- Sustained.
- No further questions.

502
00:22:57.442 --> 00:23:00.236
You have no proof
or firsthand knowledge

503
00:23:00.361 --> 00:23:03.031
that Marius Cole
tampered with or erased

504
00:23:03.156 --> 00:23:06.076
any evidence pertaining
to this case. do you?

505
00:23:06.117 --> 00:23:08.411
No. but I know
he's capable of it.

506
00:23:08.495 --> 00:23:13.124
Right. because it's a service
his company offers.

507
00:23:13.166 --> 00:23:15.543
Do you know how many employees
there are at Utomnia?

508
00:23:15.585 --> 00:23:16.669
I do not.

509
00:23:16.795 --> 00:23:19.089
4.854.

510
00:23:19.172 --> 00:23:22.258
Presumably. many of them
possess the same capabilities.

511
00:23:22.384 --> 00:23:23.927
Yes. presumably.

512
00:23:24.010 --> 00:23:27.222
And what about people
not employed by any company?

513
00:23:27.347 --> 00:23:31.559
In your experience.
are there private citizens

514
00:23:31.643 --> 00:23:35.772
that possess the skills
necessary to erase

515
00:23:35.814 --> 00:23:37.148
the data in question?

516
00:23:37.232 --> 00:23:38.483
Of course.

517
00:23:38.566 --> 00:23:40.026
And you have no knowledge
of anything

518
00:23:40.151 --> 00:23:43.029
that specifically implicates
my client

519
00:23:43.113 --> 00:23:45.198
in the murder of Natalie Wallis?

520
00:23:45.323 --> 00:23:46.741
No.

521
00:23:46.866 --> 00:23:49.911
So you're here merely
to testify to the fact

522
00:23:49.953 --> 00:23:54.249
that hacking is something
that exists in the world.

523
00:23:54.290 --> 00:23:55.708
Duly noted.

524
00:23:55.792 --> 00:23:57.293
No further questions.

525
00:24:02.090 --> 00:24:04.551
About halfway through
the meal. Natalie got a text.

526
00:24:04.676 --> 00:24:06.386
She said it was Marius

527
00:24:06.511 --> 00:24:08.138
and that she had to go back
to the office.

528
00:24:08.263 --> 00:24:09.597
Did she say why?

529
00:24:09.681 --> 00:24:11.933
No. some sort of work emergency.

530
00:24:11.975 --> 00:24:14.519
She couldn't give me the details

531
00:24:14.602 --> 00:24:16.688
because I didn't work
at the company anymore.

532
00:24:16.771 --> 00:24:22.944
Marius is brutal when it comes
to enforcing NDAs.

533
00:24:22.986 --> 00:24:25.071
So she left your dinner early.

534
00:24:25.155 --> 00:24:27.031
and she told you
that she was going

535
00:24:27.157 --> 00:24:28.742
to meet with the defendant.

536
00:24:28.867 --> 00:24:30.243
Yes.

537
00:24:30.326 --> 00:24:31.995
Do you remember
what day this was?

538
00:24:32.078 --> 00:24:34.080
October 17th.

539
00:24:34.205 --> 00:24:37.667
Thank you.
No further questions.

540
00:24:37.792 --> 00:24:40.837
We have no questions
for this witness.

541
00:24:40.879 --> 00:24:43.631
You may be excused.

542
00:24:43.715 --> 00:24:46.176
You may call
your next witness. Mr. Price.

543
00:24:46.301 --> 00:24:50.638
People call Sean Morris
to the stand.

544
00:24:50.722 --> 00:24:53.308
Did Natalie Wallis share
any details with you

545
00:24:53.433 --> 00:24:54.851
about her sexual assault?

546
00:24:54.893 --> 00:24:56.394
Objection. Hearsay.

547
00:24:56.478 --> 00:24:58.146
It speaks to Natalie Wallis's
state of mind

548
00:24:58.229 --> 00:24:59.773
at the time of her murder
and is not offered

549
00:24:59.856 --> 00:25:01.066
for the truth of the matter.

550
00:25:01.149 --> 00:25:02.150
Overruled.

551
00:25:02.275 --> 00:25:03.985
The witness may answer.

552
00:25:04.069 --> 00:25:05.695
Yes.

553
00:25:05.779 --> 00:25:08.948
She said that she was raped
by someone she knew well.

554
00:25:09.032 --> 00:25:11.201
someone she trusted.

555
00:25:11.284 --> 00:25:13.411
She said
that he gave her a drink.

556
00:25:13.536 --> 00:25:16.039
But after a few sips.
she started to feel funny.

557
00:25:16.081 --> 00:25:17.791
So she stopped drinking.

558
00:25:17.916 --> 00:25:21.044
He got mad.
insisted she drink it.

559
00:25:21.169 --> 00:25:23.588
So he tried to drug her.

560
00:25:23.671 --> 00:25:26.382
And when that didn't work.
he threw the glass

561
00:25:26.508 --> 00:25:30.011
against the wall and screamed
that he was in control.

562
00:25:30.053 --> 00:25:32.055
that she had to do what he said.

563
00:25:32.097 --> 00:25:34.724
And then what happened?

564
00:25:34.766 --> 00:25:36.768
She tried to leave.

565
00:25:36.893 --> 00:25:40.355
But he grabbed her
by the throat.

566
00:25:40.438 --> 00:25:44.067
tied her hands behind her back
with a belt.

567
00:25:44.109 --> 00:25:49.239
and then he raped her.

568
00:25:49.364 --> 00:25:53.159
She said that he whispered
in her ear the entire time.

569
00:25:53.243 --> 00:25:56.079
saying no matter how powerful
she thought she was.

570
00:25:56.162 --> 00:25:58.873
he could do
whatever he wanted to her.

571
00:25:58.998 --> 00:26:02.585
And he said other things.

572
00:26:02.669 --> 00:26:06.506
things I can't bring myself
to repeat.

573
00:26:06.631 --> 00:26:08.383
You develop a thick skin
in my line of work.

574
00:26:08.508 --> 00:26:11.678
but even I was...

575
00:26:11.803 --> 00:26:14.222
Did she tell you
when this all happened?

576
00:26:14.347 --> 00:26:16.099
October 17th.

577
00:26:16.141 --> 00:26:19.519
And did you meet with her
on the day that she was killed?

578
00:26:19.644 --> 00:26:21.146
I did.

579
00:26:21.187 --> 00:26:22.939
In our first session.
she wasn't ready

580
00:26:22.981 --> 00:26:24.816
to report her rapist.

581
00:26:24.899 --> 00:26:27.652
It's common for women
in her situation.

582
00:26:27.736 --> 00:26:31.197
especially high-powered women
in male-dominated fields.

583
00:26:31.322 --> 00:26:33.825
She was still
processing her grief.

584
00:26:33.950 --> 00:26:38.246
feeling a sense of shame.
of guilt.

585
00:26:38.329 --> 00:26:39.748
But in our last session.

586
00:26:39.789 --> 00:26:42.167
she said she was ready
to report it to the police.

587
00:26:42.250 --> 00:26:43.918
Did she tell you
when she was gonna do that?

588
00:26:44.043 --> 00:26:45.503
The next day.

589
00:26:45.628 --> 00:26:49.799
But someone killed her
before she got the chance.

590
00:26:49.841 --> 00:26:52.177
No further questions.

591
00:26:52.260 --> 00:26:55.055
Did Ms. Wallis tell you
the name of her attacker?

592
00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:56.473
No.

593
00:26:56.556 --> 00:26:58.058
She gave you all those details

594
00:26:58.141 --> 00:27:00.268
but left that one out.

595
00:27:00.351 --> 00:27:02.771
Well. like I said. she wasn't
ready to report it at first.

596
00:27:02.854 --> 00:27:06.524
And nothing you shared
specifically points

597
00:27:06.649 --> 00:27:09.736
to my client being
the one who raped her.

598
00:27:09.861 --> 00:27:13.782
In fact. because she never
sought medical attention.

599
00:27:13.823 --> 00:27:19.162
there's no factual record
that a rape even ever occurred.

600
00:27:19.245 --> 00:27:22.582
I sat with her for hours
as she shook

601
00:27:22.665 --> 00:27:28.296
with fear and rage and pain.

602
00:27:28.379 --> 00:27:30.632
I can assure you. it happened.

603
00:27:30.757 --> 00:27:33.676
That may be so.

604
00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:37.972
But my client had
nothing to do with it.

605
00:27:38.056 --> 00:27:39.890
No further questions.

606
00:27:39.890 --> 00:27:39.933
No further questions.

607
00:27:43.520 --> 00:27:45.730
Excuse me.

608
00:27:45.855 --> 00:27:47.190
Hi.

609
00:27:47.232 --> 00:27:50.443
You did great back there.

610
00:27:50.568 --> 00:27:53.363
Here.

611
00:27:53.446 --> 00:27:56.825
They always claim
mascara is waterproof.

612
00:27:56.950 --> 00:28:02.497
but in my experience.
there's no such thing.

613
00:28:02.539 --> 00:28:04.124
Thank you.

614
00:28:04.249 --> 00:28:06.126
So embarrassing.

615
00:28:06.251 --> 00:28:07.585
No.

616
00:28:07.669 --> 00:28:09.921
It's hard to hear.

617
00:28:10.004 --> 00:28:13.508
- God.
- I just keep... I...

618
00:28:13.591 --> 00:28:15.218
What?

619
00:28:15.301 --> 00:28:20.640
I'm the one who hired Natalie
to work at Utomnia.

620
00:28:20.682 --> 00:28:25.311
Of course. I didn't know
at the time that Marius...

621
00:28:25.395 --> 00:28:27.188
but she was my best friend.

622
00:28:27.272 --> 00:28:29.941
And it's my fault.
And I should have tried...

623
00:28:30.066 --> 00:28:32.402
No. don't go there. please.

624
00:28:32.444 --> 00:28:34.070
Easy for you to say.

625
00:28:34.154 --> 00:28:36.364
No. I get it.

626
00:28:36.489 --> 00:28:38.908
Trust me.

627
00:28:38.992 --> 00:28:43.079
I had a similar thing
happen to a loved one.

628
00:28:43.204 --> 00:28:46.082
I spent years
trying to blame myself.

629
00:28:49.210 --> 00:28:52.505
Marius Cole is
the monster here. not you.

630
00:28:56.134 --> 00:28:57.802
And I'm gonna do
everything I can

631
00:28:57.927 --> 00:29:01.556
to put him where he belongs.

632
00:29:01.598 --> 00:29:02.682
Thank you.

633
00:29:02.807 --> 00:29:05.477
But I... but I...

634
00:29:05.602 --> 00:29:08.897
I don't think I can watch
any more of this.

635
00:29:15.320 --> 00:29:18.031
Part of my job
as the CEO of Utomnia

636
00:29:18.114 --> 00:29:21.076
is cultivating new business.
which means wining and dining

637
00:29:21.159 --> 00:29:22.869
the people in charge
of handing out

638
00:29:22.911 --> 00:29:25.371
government and private
defense contracts.

639
00:29:25.455 --> 00:29:27.082
Last year.
I had a potential client

640
00:29:27.207 --> 00:29:29.834
that wanted to discuss business
on a shooting range.

641
00:29:29.918 --> 00:29:31.795
The range made you
purchase ammunition.

642
00:29:31.920 --> 00:29:33.296
and I ended up with extra.

643
00:29:33.421 --> 00:29:35.215
So that's why the police found

644
00:29:35.340 --> 00:29:37.634
9 millimeter bullets
in your home.

645
00:29:37.759 --> 00:29:40.637
Yeah. but I don't even have
a gun to shoot them with.

646
00:29:40.720 --> 00:29:43.640
I've never fired a weapon
outside of a shooting range.

647
00:29:43.765 --> 00:29:47.227
Marius. did you rape
Natalie Wallis?

648
00:29:47.268 --> 00:29:48.770
God. no.

649
00:29:48.812 --> 00:29:50.855
The prosecution is claiming
that was your motive

650
00:29:50.939 --> 00:29:53.066
for wanting her dead.
that she was going

651
00:29:53.191 --> 00:29:55.235
to report you
for assaulting her.

652
00:29:55.360 --> 00:29:56.903
That's insane.

653
00:29:56.986 --> 00:29:59.447
I would never harm a woman.

654
00:29:59.489 --> 00:30:02.450
I have spent real money and time

655
00:30:02.534 --> 00:30:05.370
not only in programs
supporting women in STEM

656
00:30:05.453 --> 00:30:07.622
but in making sure
that my companies are a place

657
00:30:07.705 --> 00:30:09.541
where women can feel safe

658
00:30:09.624 --> 00:30:12.043
and have access
to equal opportunities.

659
00:30:12.085 --> 00:30:14.421
But your DNA was in her home.

660
00:30:14.504 --> 00:30:16.548
And as the prosecution
pointed out.

661
00:30:16.673 --> 00:30:19.217
you were both diagnosed
with hepatitis B.

662
00:30:19.259 --> 00:30:22.220
That's correct.

663
00:30:22.303 --> 00:30:25.306
When I told Natalie
about my diagnosis.

664
00:30:25.348 --> 00:30:28.017
she was very upset.

665
00:30:28.143 --> 00:30:30.186
She had recently been
diagnosed as well

666
00:30:30.311 --> 00:30:32.981
but was afraid to tell me.

667
00:30:33.064 --> 00:30:34.774
What are you saying?

668
00:30:34.858 --> 00:30:37.777
I contracted it from her.

669
00:30:37.861 --> 00:30:40.155
Natalie and I had been seeing
each other for a few months

670
00:30:40.238 --> 00:30:42.949
before she was killed.

671
00:30:43.032 --> 00:30:44.909
We kept
the relationship private.

672
00:30:44.951 --> 00:30:48.788
Which explains why
your DNA was in her home.

673
00:30:48.913 --> 00:30:52.000
Were you dating
at the time of the murder?

674
00:30:52.083 --> 00:30:55.962
No. I called it off
about a week before.

675
00:30:56.087 --> 00:30:58.715
We weren't connecting.

676
00:30:58.798 --> 00:31:01.217
Now I know why.

677
00:31:01.342 --> 00:31:04.971
She didn't tell me
she had been raped.

678
00:31:05.055 --> 00:31:07.557
If she had.
I never would have...

679
00:31:07.599 --> 00:31:09.893
we could have gotten
through that together.

680
00:31:09.976 --> 00:31:12.937
I wish more than anything
that we had.

681
00:31:13.063 --> 00:31:14.647
Thank you.

682
00:31:14.731 --> 00:31:16.900
No further questions.

683
00:31:18.818 --> 00:31:24.032
If you and Ms. Wallis
had been

684
00:31:24.074 --> 00:31:27.160
seeing each other. as you claim.

685
00:31:27.243 --> 00:31:28.703
why not mention that
to the police

686
00:31:28.787 --> 00:31:30.622
when they first spoke to you?

687
00:31:30.663 --> 00:31:32.332
I didn't think it was relevant.

688
00:31:32.457 --> 00:31:35.710
I had no information about who
her killer could have been.

689
00:31:35.835 --> 00:31:40.882
and I was grieving the loss
of somebody that I loved.

690
00:31:40.924 --> 00:31:42.717
It was personal.

691
00:31:42.801 --> 00:31:44.052
Private.

692
00:31:44.177 --> 00:31:46.471
So you loved Natalie?

693
00:31:46.513 --> 00:31:49.516
Did you ever tell anyone that...

694
00:31:49.557 --> 00:31:52.519
you ever tell them that the two
of you were in a relationship?

695
00:31:52.644 --> 00:31:53.853
No. it was...

696
00:31:53.937 --> 00:31:55.688
No. it was private. Right.

697
00:31:55.814 --> 00:31:57.232
Sorry. How convenient.

698
00:31:57.315 --> 00:31:59.359
But I can provide
plenty of data that shows

699
00:31:59.484 --> 00:32:01.611
that we were spending nights
and weekends together.

700
00:32:01.653 --> 00:32:03.321
messages that we sent
each other.

701
00:32:03.405 --> 00:32:04.406
Things that we've
already established

702
00:32:04.489 --> 00:32:05.990
that you can fabricate.

703
00:32:06.116 --> 00:32:08.993
But I'm guessing
that not a single person...

704
00:32:09.119 --> 00:32:12.455
I mean. a real. live person

705
00:32:12.497 --> 00:32:14.916
can actually corroborate
your story.

706
00:32:15.041 --> 00:32:17.335
a story which just so happens
to explain away

707
00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:19.504
all the evidence against you.

708
00:32:19.587 --> 00:32:22.674
almost as if it were crafted
to do exactly that.

709
00:32:22.715 --> 00:32:25.176
Objection. Your Honor.
Argumentative.

710
00:32:25.301 --> 00:32:28.680
Sustained.
Move on. Mr. Price.

711
00:32:28.763 --> 00:32:30.265
You forced yourself
on Natalie. didn't you?

712
00:32:30.390 --> 00:32:31.599
- No.
- You raped her.

713
00:32:31.683 --> 00:32:33.476
And then you kept tabs on her.

714
00:32:33.518 --> 00:32:34.894
That's what you do. isn't it?

715
00:32:35.019 --> 00:32:37.355
With your spyware and your
high-tech surveillance.

716
00:32:37.397 --> 00:32:40.483
you figured out that she was
gonna go to the police.

717
00:32:40.525 --> 00:32:43.945
And so you killed her.

718
00:32:44.070 --> 00:32:47.615
I have never raped anybody
in my entire life.

719
00:32:47.741 --> 00:32:51.119
And I swear to you.
I did not kill Natalie.

720
00:32:51.202 --> 00:32:53.621
But I would kill the man
who did if I could.

721
00:33:00.044 --> 00:33:01.713
How valiant.

722
00:33:01.770 --> 00:33:04.507
No further questions
for this witness.

723
00:33:11.241 --> 00:33:12.528
Yes.

724
00:33:13.311 --> 00:33:15.855
No. no.
You've been very helpful.

725
00:33:16.227 --> 00:33:18.012
Thank you so much.

726
00:33:18.037 --> 00:33:20.209
That was the shooting range
where Cole claims

727
00:33:20.234 --> 00:33:21.505
he bought the ammunition.

728
00:33:21.530 --> 00:33:24.408
Confirmed he was there
last spring with a client.

729
00:33:24.728 --> 00:33:26.939
All that proves is that
he knows how to shoot a gun

730
00:33:26.964 --> 00:33:28.005
and had bullets.

731
00:33:28.030 --> 00:33:32.513
I'm worried that his story
is just plausible enough

732
00:33:32.538 --> 00:33:34.123
to buy him reasonable doubt.

733
00:33:34.248 --> 00:33:38.628
Plus. there's that fake video
of him being home all night.

734
00:33:38.711 --> 00:33:42.215
We need to find a way
to prove that he is lying.

735
00:33:42.240 --> 00:33:45.275
Well. what we need
is another victim.

736
00:33:45.872 --> 00:33:49.584
Guys like this.
they don't just do it once.

737
00:33:49.609 --> 00:33:51.611
I agree. but police tried
to find other victims.

738
00:33:51.636 --> 00:33:52.637
They came up empty.

739
00:33:52.957 --> 00:33:54.459
Yeah.

740
00:33:54.643 --> 00:33:57.271
He loves to make people
sign NDAs.

741
00:33:57.605 --> 00:34:01.109
Maybe that's how he's been able
to keep other victims quiet?

742
00:34:01.134 --> 00:34:03.770
Yeah. I know
it's a thing that happens.

743
00:34:03.887 --> 00:34:05.129
I do.

744
00:34:05.887 --> 00:34:08.257
But as a woman.
I just can't imagine

745
00:34:08.282 --> 00:34:11.077
letting a known predator
continue to operate

746
00:34:11.119 --> 00:34:12.794
in exchange for money.

747
00:34:12.819 --> 00:34:16.489
If it helps at all.
it's probably a lot of money.

748
00:34:16.921 --> 00:34:18.714
I don't care
how much he offered.

749
00:34:18.739 --> 00:34:22.702
How can someone. a woman.
live with that kind of guilt?

750
00:34:29.036 --> 00:34:31.455
Sam?

751
00:34:31.597 --> 00:34:32.932
What is it?

752
00:34:37.353 --> 00:34:39.397
Cole assaulted you. too.
didn't he?

753
00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:43.359
That's... where...
where is this coming from?

754
00:34:43.443 --> 00:34:44.944
You didn't answer my question.

755
00:34:45.069 --> 00:34:46.863
The answer is no.

756
00:34:46.988 --> 00:34:49.824
And I would like you
to leave. please.

757
00:34:51.743 --> 00:34:55.747
It's okay. Vanessa.
You can be honest with me.

758
00:34:55.788 --> 00:34:58.750
No. I can't.

759
00:34:58.875 --> 00:35:01.377
Because you signed
a nondisclosure agreement?

760
00:35:07.175 --> 00:35:09.761
Well. how much did he pay you

761
00:35:09.844 --> 00:35:12.972
to serve up your best friend
on a platter?

762
00:35:13.014 --> 00:35:14.140
I didn't serve up anything.

763
00:35:14.265 --> 00:35:15.767
You left her vulnerable.

764
00:35:15.808 --> 00:35:17.351
You didn't warn her.

765
00:35:20.063 --> 00:35:24.609
I don't owe you any explanation.

766
00:35:24.692 --> 00:35:25.985
But it wasn't about the money.

767
00:35:26.069 --> 00:35:28.654
I was humiliated.

768
00:35:28.696 --> 00:35:30.364
I didn't want anyone to know.

769
00:35:30.448 --> 00:35:32.700
I wanted...

770
00:35:32.784 --> 00:35:34.327
I didn't wanna spend
the rest of my life

771
00:35:34.410 --> 00:35:38.372
being defined
by what he did to me.

772
00:35:38.414 --> 00:35:41.667
I wanted it to go away forever.

773
00:35:41.751 --> 00:35:43.878
Leaving him to be
the next woman's problem.

774
00:35:44.003 --> 00:35:46.297
No. he swore to me he'd never
done anything like that before.

775
00:35:46.339 --> 00:35:48.299
and I believed him.

776
00:35:48.424 --> 00:35:50.843
I let myself believe him.

777
00:35:50.927 --> 00:35:53.221
So I took the money.
I found a new job.

778
00:35:53.346 --> 00:35:59.352
and I did everything I could

779
00:35:59.435 --> 00:36:02.188
to put that horrible moment
behind me.

780
00:36:02.313 --> 00:36:06.442
It is what I needed to do.

781
00:36:08.611 --> 00:36:11.739
Well. right now.

782
00:36:11.781 --> 00:36:14.409
what you need to do is testify.

783
00:36:14.492 --> 00:36:16.452
No. no. I can't.

784
00:36:16.577 --> 00:36:19.038
Don't worry.
Your money is safe.

785
00:36:19.122 --> 00:36:21.582
NDAs are not enforceable
when testifying about a crime.

786
00:36:21.707 --> 00:36:23.000
It's not about the money.

787
00:36:23.126 --> 00:36:25.795
If people find out
that I didn't come forward.

788
00:36:25.878 --> 00:36:28.923
that I took the money.

789
00:36:29.006 --> 00:36:30.883
my career is over.

790
00:36:31.008 --> 00:36:32.635
The press will crucify me.

791
00:36:32.760 --> 00:36:34.220
I will be...

792
00:36:34.262 --> 00:36:37.265
I will be the enemy
of all women.

793
00:36:37.348 --> 00:36:41.227
I work for a company
focused on women's health.

794
00:36:41.310 --> 00:36:42.812
for Christ's sake.

795
00:36:42.937 --> 00:36:44.772
Everyone will look at me

796
00:36:44.856 --> 00:36:47.817
the way you're looking at me
right now.

797
00:36:49.736 --> 00:36:51.779
Price you pay for taking
the money. I suppose.

798
00:36:51.863 --> 00:36:53.698
That is not fair.

799
00:36:53.823 --> 00:36:56.701
All I have done is pay.

800
00:36:56.826 --> 00:37:00.747
every day. every night.

801
00:37:08.629 --> 00:37:13.426
I took... I took the money

802
00:37:13.468 --> 00:37:16.971
because it felt right.

803
00:37:17.013 --> 00:37:18.514
I don't even know
how to describe it.

804
00:37:18.598 --> 00:37:23.061
When he came to me
with that offer.

805
00:37:23.186 --> 00:37:25.521
I was struggling.

806
00:37:25.605 --> 00:37:28.483
He had ripped my life apart.

807
00:37:31.611 --> 00:37:33.738
I was just trying to survive.

808
00:37:42.789 --> 00:37:45.333
You said something like this
happened to someone you loved?

809
00:37:51.464 --> 00:37:53.299
My sister.

810
00:37:56.803 --> 00:38:00.515
When it happened.
who were you worried about?

811
00:38:00.598 --> 00:38:03.476
Her.

812
00:38:03.559 --> 00:38:08.439
or some
hypothetical future victim?

813
00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:16.572
We'll subpoena her.
force her to take the stand.

814
00:38:16.656 --> 00:38:18.449
Even if we have to treat her
as a hostile witness.

815
00:38:18.574 --> 00:38:20.910
her testimony will likely
get us a conviction.

816
00:38:20.952 --> 00:38:22.578
I agree.

817
00:38:22.703 --> 00:38:24.789
I understand Ms. Barret not
wanting to be publicly shamed.

818
00:38:24.872 --> 00:38:27.166
but we're talking about putting
a murderer behind bars here.

819
00:38:27.250 --> 00:38:28.960
Yeah. I get it.

820
00:38:29.085 --> 00:38:32.880
Respectfully. more than
either of you. but I...

821
00:38:33.005 --> 00:38:34.841
But what?

822
00:38:34.924 --> 00:38:36.551
I don't know.

823
00:38:36.634 --> 00:38:40.972
I mean. what she said to me
was very compelling.

824
00:38:41.055 --> 00:38:43.099
Are we really gonna further
punish a woman

825
00:38:43.182 --> 00:38:45.601
who's already been through
so much?

826
00:38:45.685 --> 00:38:47.353
Marius Cole's a sexual predator

827
00:38:47.478 --> 00:38:49.230
and a cold-blooded killer.

828
00:38:49.272 --> 00:38:51.315
We have a duty
to protect the public.

829
00:38:51.399 --> 00:38:53.109
to stop him
from victimizing anyone else.

830
00:38:53.234 --> 00:38:56.529
At the expense of someone
he's already victimized.

831
00:38:56.612 --> 00:38:58.197
And what about our duty to her?

832
00:38:58.281 --> 00:39:00.116
Sam. come on.
You said it yourself.

833
00:39:00.241 --> 00:39:02.952
This woman took a payout
in exchange for her silence.

834
00:39:03.035 --> 00:39:04.328
And it got another woman killed.

835
00:39:04.454 --> 00:39:05.997
I know.

836
00:39:06.122 --> 00:39:09.834
But I think there's another way
we can handle this.

837
00:39:26.434 --> 00:39:29.353
We are open to a plea.

838
00:39:29.395 --> 00:39:30.855
No. thank you.

839
00:39:30.938 --> 00:39:33.149
All rise
for the Honorable Judge Dillow.

840
00:39:35.526 --> 00:39:36.736
Court is now in session.

841
00:39:36.861 --> 00:39:38.988
You may be seated.

842
00:39:39.072 --> 00:39:41.365
Mr. Price. I understand
you have a point of order?

843
00:39:41.491 --> 00:39:43.159
Yes. Your Honor.
the prosecution would like

844
00:39:43.242 --> 00:39:45.036
to call a rebuttal witness.

845
00:39:45.161 --> 00:39:46.704
Vanessa Barret.

846
00:40:02.929 --> 00:40:05.348
Man 1. and we've got a deal.

847
00:40:10.520 --> 00:40:12.271
We're open to murder 2.

848
00:40:14.816 --> 00:40:17.110
Your Honor. we'd like
to request a recess.

849
00:40:21.239 --> 00:40:23.658
Cole agreed to plead guilty
to second-degree murder

850
00:40:23.783 --> 00:40:25.910
with a recommended sentence
of 20 years.

851
00:40:26.035 --> 00:40:27.412
It's not ideal.

852
00:40:27.495 --> 00:40:29.705
But it guarantees
he'll be in his late 60s

853
00:40:29.789 --> 00:40:32.333
before he even has a chance
to see the light of day again.

854
00:40:32.375 --> 00:40:36.754
I... I appreciate
what you did.

855
00:40:36.796 --> 00:40:38.339
I really do.

856
00:40:43.761 --> 00:40:45.012
What would you have done

857
00:40:45.054 --> 00:40:46.973
if Cole's lawyer didn't take
the bait?

858
00:40:49.851 --> 00:40:51.436
I'm just glad it all worked out.

858
